<paragraph blockId="18.[813,1455,1530,1607]" pageId="18" pageNumber="179">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brignoli" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[961,1161,1530,1554]" class="Arachnida" family="Dipluridae" genus="Linothele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melloleitaoi">
<emphasis box="[961,1161,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="179">Linothele melloleitaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2015" box="[1264,1339,1531,1554]" class="Arachnida" family="Dipluridae" genus="Linothele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quori">
<emphasis box="[1264,1339,1531,1554]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="179">L. quori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and may be distinguished from it by its flexible leg tarsi, the absence of a ventral pattern from the opisthosoma, alongside its distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
